Paris Saint-Germain defender Thiago Silva is awarded the 2012 Samba Gold trophy, a football award given to the best Brazilian footballer in Europe. (Sambafoot)Galatasaray nearly overthrow Real Madrid 3–2 during a surprising second half in Istanbul. Galatasaray's goals fly in from Emmanuel Eboué, Wesley Sneijder and Didier Drogba, but Cristiano Ronaldo score twice and Real Madrid win 5–3 on aggregate in the end, progressing to the semi-final stage for a record 24th time. (The Guardian) (BBC) (UEFA)